title: The Amsterdam Dungeon Entrance Ticket

title: Rotterdam + Kinderdijk: All Inclusive, Guided Private Tour in Rotterdam
Zaanse Schans 3-Hour Private Tour from central Amsterdam, Airport or Port

Stop at the historical, windmill village of Zaanse Schan and take a guided tour around the pretty lanes and watersides, passing green-painted houses, wooden barns and shops. Watch clogs and cheese being made at craft workshops, and visit a working windmill to learn how they were used to pump water, saw wood and more through the 17th and 18th centuries.

title: Zaanse Schans Windmills, Clogs and Dutch Cheese Small-Group Tour from Amsterdam

Take a tour of pretty Zaanse Schans, famous for its wooden windmills and green-painted houses, and visit a cheese farm and clog-making workshop to learn about these traditional crafts. Lastly, visit a working windmill to learn how these waterside factories helped drive the 17th-century Dutch Golden Age. Numbers are limited on this tour for a small-group experience.

Learn about the international flavors that have influenced Dutch cuisine while grabbing bites at a local market. Savor handpicked local delicacies including the best fish in town, a sweet ‘stroopwafel’ and unique dishes typical of the city such as bitterballen. This culinary tour in Amsterdam is a cultural journey that takes you further than the food you’ll eat. Stop to admire the Banksy street art, De Pijp, and Museumplein and many other city highlights.

Gain insight into the city’s liberal sex industry, and find out about the city’s thriving café culture. Admission to the Sex Museum is included.

Stay clear of the crowds as you cruise through areas such as Jordaan and Vondelpark, and benefit from your small-group guide's personalized attention and insights as you visit landmarks including the Anne Frank House and Brouwerij 't IJ. Breeze past the main entrance lines and explore the collections as you wish, seeing masterpieces such as Rembrandt’s ‘Night Watch’ and fascinating exhibitions on Dutch history.
